headline: Cocoa Prices Stabilize as Dollar Tumbles
summary: December ICE NY cocoa (CCZ25 ) on Friday closed up +72 (+0.97%), and December ICE London cocoa #7 (CAZ25 ) closed up +5 (+0.10%). Dec NY cocoa traded higher Friday, recovering a bit after Thursday's plunge of -3.52%. Cocoa prices saw some support Friday from short-covering and the sharp decline...

headline: Pepsi Has Lost Its Bubbles. Elliott Wants to Make It Pop Again.
summary: PepsiCo  has lost its fizz, and activist investor Elliott Investment Management sees an opening to push for a turnaround.  Elliott, a hedge fund with about $76 billion in assets, on Sept. 2 said it had taken a $4 billion stake in  PepsiCo  pressing for changes at the struggling snack-and-beverage giant.  The stake accounts for about 2% of PepsiCo’s market capitalization and makes Elliott one of the company’s largest investors.
